               <head>'Amal-i Salih</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of ʿAmal-i Ṣāliḥ by Muḥammad Ṣāliḥ Kanbū Lāhawrī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n50002533 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115921 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3907-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656954.0x000001 viaf_270970434">Muḥammad Ṣāliḥ Kanbū Lāhawrī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656954.0x000001 viaf_270970434" type="supplied">محمّد صالح كنبو لاهورى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7110">ʿAmal-i Ṣāliḥ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_7110">عمل صالح</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Alternative title: <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Shāhjahānnāmah</term>
                        </p>
                        <p>An abridged <term xml:lang="en">history</term> of the genealogy, princehood, succession, and reign of the Mughal Emperor  <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656355.0x000001 viaf_13108102" role="subject">Shāh Jahān</persName> (d. <date calendar="Gregorian">1666</date>).
                        </p>
                        <p>Early portions of this account (up to year 11) are based on earlier (abrogated) official <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Pādshāhnāmahs</term>, especially works by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_15147663108860552472" role="ant">Muḥammad Amīn Qazvīnī</persName> and <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_2380388" role="ant">Mīrzā Jalāl al-Dīn Muḥammad Ṭabāṭabāʾī</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Later portions of this account (years 11-31) are based on later official <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Pādshāhnāmahs</term>, especially works by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_77040323" role="ant">Shaykh ʿAbd al-Ḥamīd Lāhawrī</persName> and <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7722" role="ant">Muḥammad Vāris̲ Vāris̲ Khān</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>The account concludes with important information of the emperor's overthrow by Prince <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_6178410" role="pat">Awrangzīb</persName>, later <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_6178410" role="pat">ʿĀlamgīr Pādshāh I</persName> (d. <date calendar="Gregorian">1707</date>)
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
